@notice Initialize a new SparseMerkleUtils contract, computing the default hashes
 for the sparse merkle tree (SMT) and saving them as a contract.

@notice Initialize a new SparseMerkleUtils contract, computing the default hashes
 for the sparse merkle tree (SMT) and saving them as a contract.

params._dataBlocks: The data being used to generate the tree.

params._index: The index of the bit we want to extract
params._intVal: The uint we are extracting a bit out of

returns._0: The bit (1 or 0) in a uint8

params._dataBlock: The data block we're verifying inclusion for.
params._path: The path from the leaf to the root.
params._root: The root of the tree we are verifying inclusion for.
params._siblings: The sibling nodes along the way.

returns._0: The next level of the tree

verifyAndUpdate(bytes32,bytes,bytes,uint.details: Verify an inclusion proof for a sparse merkle tree, where some of the siblings are not included because they are default nodes, and simultaneously calculate the root using an alternative leaf node.

params._path: The path from the leaf to the root.
params._proveData: The data block we're verifying inclusion for.
params._root: The root of the tree we are verifying inclusion for.
params._setData: The data block we're replacing _proveData with.
params._siblings: The sibling nodes along the way.

returns._valid: Boolean stating whether the proof was valid.

verifyAndUpdateSparse(bytes32,uint256,ui.details: Verify an inclusion proof for a sparse merkle tree, where some of the siblings are not included because they are default nodes, and simultaneously calculate the root using an alternative leaf node.

params._height: The height of the tree the proof is for.
params._inclusionBits: Bit field indicating which siblings are included as siblings.
params._path: The path from the leaf to the root.
params._proveData: The data block we're verifying inclusion for.
params._root: The root of the tree we are verifying inclusion for.
params._setData: The data block we're replacing _proveData with.
params._siblings: The sibling nodes along the way.

returns._valid: Boolean stating whether the proof was valid.

verifySparse(bytes32,uint256,uint256,byt.details: Verify an inclusion proof for a sparse merkle tree, where some of the siblings are not included because they are default nodes.

params._height: The height of the tree the proof is for.
params._inclusionBits: Bit field indicating which siblings are included as siblings.
params._leaf: The data block we're verifying inclusion for.
params._path: The path from the leaf to the root.
params._root: The root of the tree we are verifying inclusion for.
params._siblings: The sibling nodes along the way.

returns._0: The next level of the tree

methods.constructor: Initialize a new SparseMerkleUtils contract, computing the default hashes for the sparse merkle tree (SMT) and saving them as a contract.

getMerkleRoot(bytes[]).notice: Get the sparse merkle root computed from some set of data blocks.

getNthBitFromRight(uint256,uint256).notice: get the n'th bit in a uint.         For instance, if exampleUint=binary(11), getNth(exampleUint, 0) == 1, getNth(2, 1) == 1
